author: rooneg
msg: Don't depend on libneon.la being installed on the system, as some packaged
versions of neon (notably FreeBSD's port and some RPM's) do not necessarily
(SVN_DOWNLOAD_NEON): rather than stripping -lneon from the output of
'neon_config --libs' and then using that and the location we assume
libneon.la will be in as NEON_LIBS, just use the unmodified output of
'neon_config --libs', since we will be handing it off to libtool
anyway, and it will do the right thing with regards to using the .la
file if it can find it.
